headline: Airline Stocks Rally After Delta Says Demand Is Stabilizing
summary: U.S. airline stocks rose sharply on Thursday after Delta Air Lines said travel demand has stabilized.  Shares of Delta, American Airlines and United Airlines were up 12%, 13% and 14%, respectively at the end of the trading day.  The U.S. Global Jets ETF, which tracks an index of various airlines, rose about 7% to the highest level since February, according to Dow Jones Market Data.
